properties.Mission: Our Mission is to eliminate barriers to full equality for people with disabilities through programs which promote independent living and effect systems change, while honoring dignity and self determination.

Booktown is a cooperative of 14 independent book sellers with 4,000 square feet of Used and Rare Books, Ephemera, Books on CDs, Music CDs, DVDs, LP Records and Art. We have added a new Rare Book Room where discriminating collectors can find fabulous rare, unusual and antiquarian books.

properties.Organization: Boys and Girls Club of North Lake Tahoe
properties.Mission: Our mission is to inspire and enable all youth, especially those who need us most, to reach their full potential as productive, caring, responsible citizens.

The Community Collaborative of Tahoe Truckee (CCTT) is a partnership of nonprofit and public organizations working together to address fundamental needs of families in the Tahoe Truckee Region. Collectively, we identify emerging community issues and develop strategies with our combined vision and resources.

The NCERC is committed to ensuring a thriving, attractive business environment in Nevada County. We support scalable ventures that create quality jobs, promote entrepreneurship, help existing businesses, attract new businesses, and contribute to the overall prosperity of the community.  Our organization provides a platform for dialogue and collaboration to create strong, informed strategies for Nevada County’s economic ecosystem.
To promote social and economic success in our community by providing education, mobilizing resources and advocating for change.

Friends of the Truckee Library is a nonprofit organization dedicated to promoting and providing support for the Truckee Library as an essential institution of society. Our members advocate, educate and raise funds on behalf of the library. We are a dedicated group of active volunteers that have spent decades devoted to growing and sustaining the Truckee Library.

The Golden Road Radio and Television Show explores the intersection of the arts and culture, the environment, health, peace and justice and science and technology. We are dedicated to building a better future through education, individual empowerment, community building and positive social change.

I lead small (less than 6) groups of keen photographers on guided workshops to destinations around the globe. My trips are custom tailored to offer the perfect balance of adventure, photography, and learning
To serve our members by facilitating business development, promoting tourism and visitor direction and presenting information that supports responsible business growth in our community.
The Grass Valley Downtown Association shall represent its general membership with a unified voice in economic development and historical preservation of downtown Grass Valley and our community

The High Fives Foundation supports the dreams of outdoor action sports athletes by raising injury prevention awareness while providing resources and inspiration to those who suffer life altering injuries.
Hour Nevada County is an hour exchange based on the equality of time, empowering individuals to utilize their assets and enhance their lives, neighborhood and community.

We are a collaborative kitchen space and culinary incubator available for rent to caterers, private chefs, food production companies, food trucks, food educators, and health professionals. Our Mission is to elevate and strengthen the Truckee Tahoe food economy by supporting its food entrepreneurs.
Nevada County’s first choice for local news.

Our Mission is to entertain and inform the local community. We are independent so we can play and talk about what you want to hear. Our format is Triple A, which means we play a wide variety of music.
KVMR provides community members opportunities to connect through the development and production of music, news, and public affairs programs that entertain, inform, and educate.

Moonshine Ink brings you Tahoe news straight from the source. Our team of hardworking journalists uncovers North Tahoe and Truckee news stories with in depth reporting and our authentic for the community, by the community spirit.

The Nevada City Advocate is a local, woman owned monthly community newspaper.  Nevada County's only free newspaper that covers entertainment, people you know and should know, city government, county government and the issues you care about.

The Nevada City Rotary Club is the service club people want to join because it’s a diverse and welcoming group of people who live Service Above Self by giving financial and hands-on support to our local, national and international communities, exemplify ethical leadership, and get things done while having good, clean fun.

properties.Organization: Nevada City School of the Arts
properties.Mission: We see our role as facilitators of the Arts in the community, enriching it with dance and theater, exhibitions and performances, collaborating with other artists, promoting and assisting the vision of arts-based education with other educational entities.
The Nevada County Digital Media Center is Nevada County’s hub for all things film & video. Creation, Collaboration, Learning & Distribution!

In August 1972, the Nevada County Library System was incorporated, with the Nevada City library serving as the main branch.  Today the system includes the Grass Valley Library, the Truckee Library. the Doris Foley Library for Historical Research. The Bear River Library (a partnership with the Bear River High School Library) and Penn Valley Library (located in a shopping center) were added in 2002.
To foster community dialogue, increase civic engagement, and enrich the cultural life of our community through television, the internet, and other digital media.

Nevada Union has more to offer than any other comprehensive high school in the region.  There is something here for everyone, and each provides an opportunity to shine. Whether it's academics, sports, dance, choir, AG metals, farming, drama, band, or woodworking,  the list goes on.

Our mission is to promote and stimulate business growth and development to benefit area businesses and the communities they serve. To facilitate our mission, we are continually broadening our media outreach through community involvement and radio, TV, and newspaper coverage, in addition to application of the Internet and distribution of electronic media.

properties.Organization: Rough and Ready Chamber of Commerce
properties.Mission: Rough and Ready is located in Nevada County, California, just a short drive west of Grass Valley.  Rough and Ready provides ideal country living with proximity to outdoor recreational activities, and yet we are reasonably close to metropolitan areas.

The Searls Historical Library is the archive of the Nevada County Historical Society. Established in 1973, the Searls Library has become one of the premier libraries of materials on the area's history, people and mines which contributed to the development of this county.

Sierra Business Council pioneers and demonstrates innovative approaches and solutions to increase community vitality, economic prosperity, environmental quality, and social fairness in the Sierra Nevada.

Since its first days, the promise of Sierra College has been to facilitate learning, inspire change, and build community. The College continues this mission as it adapts to meet the ever changing needs of students while promoting learning as a lifelong process.

Sierra FoodWineArt is a free, quarterly lifestyle magazine that is the go-to publication for restaurants, wineries, wine & beer, arts & music, and travel & tourism in the Sierra Foothills, Tahoe/Truckee, Reno and outlying Sacramento region. We also have a companion website called SierraCulture.com.
Sierra Harvest’s mission is to educate, inspire, and connect Nevada County families to fresh, local, seasonal food.

properties.Organization: South Nevada County Chamber of Commerce
properties.Mission: The Chamber’s mission statement is to provide a voice for the business community and enhance the economic vitality of South Nevada County. As our membership continues to grow and flourish, the Chamber will continue to work with our local businesses and the community, bringing vitality to the South Nevada County area.

Tahoe Donner is a recreational oriented mountain residential community whose mutual benefit association of 6,500 owners provides for the standards, regular operation and long term maintenance of programs, facilities and open space.
Our mission is to end the incidence and trauma of intimate partner and domestic violence, sexual violence, and child abuse in North Lake Tahoe and Truckee.
Tahoe Truckee Community Foundation connects people and opportunities, generating resources to build a more caring, creative, and effective community.
We are a full-service independent bookstore located in historic downtown Grass Valley, the heart of California's Gold Country.

properties.Organization: The Center for Non Profit Leadership
properties.Mission: The Center for Nonprofit Leadership (CNL) is a resource center for organizations and individuals in Nevada County and the Sierra Nevada region of California. Founded in 2003 as a catalyst to strengthen and sustain local nonprofit organizations, CNL focuses on best practice workshops, executive leadership seminars, on-site coaching and mentoring, and public advocacy.

The Golden Road radio television show explores the intersection of the arts, the environment, culture, health, and technology. We are building a better future through education, community building and positive social change.

Tomes Bookstore was founded in Nevada City, California in 1994, then moved to Maltman Drive in Grass Valley in 1997. Under new ownership in 2015, the store’s name was changed to the Open Book, with a new emphasis on events at night, and a new collective model, while honoring the same book and community based ethos during the day.
Covering the arts.

The Union is is one of the oldest daily newspapers in California. It was founded in 1864, as the Civil War raged and people in Nevada County were divided. The Union made its stand clear: For The Union, One and Inseparable. Those words have appeared on its front page every day since then.

Creating the best future for our community requires the highest level of public service every day. We will accomplish that in partnership with the Town’s citizens and our fellow governmental agencies.
Our mission is to promote and develop local business and tourism while improving the community's quality of life.

The vision of Truckee Downtown Merchants Association (TDMA) is to create, support and sustain a vibrant and visible downtown through solid membership, community collaboration and unique events; ensuring a vital, art-filled and welcoming authentic Historic Downtown Truckee for residents and visitors alike.
The mission of Truckee Tahoe Community Television is to provide a PEG Access Television Center to the residents of Truckee and North Tahoe, CA at limited cost.
Word After Word Books is a welcoming space for the community and visitors to connect around books. The Word After Word Team hosts author events, writing workshops, book clubs, and story times.
Dedicated to establishing a Penn Valley Cultural Center, a centrally located facility for all ages and interests.

KYRR is a licensed non-profit public safety community radio station operated by Yuba River Radio, a community radio club, broadcasting 24/7 programs as diverse as heavy metal, trance, world, classic rock, punk, hip-hop, and pop music with a focus on local artists.

At Truckee Tahoe Community Television our mission is to foster community awareness and communication through local programming from individuals, groups and agencies. We serve the Truckee, North Tahoe area with interesting and informative programs through Suddenlink Channel 6, Channel 18 and online video streaming. We instruct the general public, and TTUSD students in particular, in the motion picture arts and sciences.
